begin_memory_text: We talked about where we're located, what we do for jobs, and some about travel and cost of living in our respective areas
middle_memory_text: Travel, travel experiences, Covid, etc. And told each other a lot about things that went wrong while travelling
end_memory_text: More about travel, she talked about going around Eastern Europe, I focused on my time in Mexico and asia
rest_of_day_open: I think it'll go well! I have work and pickleball, and Georgetown Law results begin to come out on Friday. I'm hoping to get in, so I'm excited to hear back. I'm also excited to go to Goodwill sometime this week and get a decorative bowl to put some pumkins in
critical_positive: We were both friendly and seemed ready to chat. It was helpful that we were both younger people, and lived on the same coast so we were familiar with each other's geography. I think it was also helpful that we've both travelled a lot, because that became a main point of conversation.
critical_negative: Not much! I think it was mainly normal zoom issues, like talking over each other accidentally or that kind of thing. I think we'd get along very well in person. I could have talked a little bit less, but I think we were fairly evenly split. It was overall a good conversation.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning, we mainly talked about where we were from, school, and work. We were just starting to get to know each other a bit and learn about each other's backgrounds.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we were mainly just exchanging stories. We were mostly talking about the pandemic and living costs, and eventually we started talking about travel.
end_memory_text: Toward the end of the conversation, we were talking about our most accident prone travel moments. We exchanged a couple stories about funny but also scary travel times. We also finally introduced ourselves!
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to go really well. I have some exciting plans for the week and the weekend. I get to spend time with my friends and my family, which always makes me happy. And, I have a peaceful home that ensures even my more relaxed days are lovely too.
critical_positive: I think jumping right into the conversation and finding commonalities worked really well for the conversation. Plus, this allowed us to avoid the awkward introduction phase that can sometimes happen in a conversation. I also think focusing on those commonalities, approaching things with curiosity, and sharing stories back and forth worked really well.
critical_negative: Honestly, I think the conversation was great and I don't think there was anything that didn't work super well. I guess the only thing that made it less than optimal is, unlike real life, there isn't really an expectation of talking to each other or seeing each other again, which can make conversations feel pointless for some individuals. I just like getting to know new people, so I don't mind that!
